Chill until partially set.
Soften cream cheese; stir in pimiento.
Add to gelatin mixture and blend.
Fold in whipped cream, celery and nuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash and onions.
Stir in 5 tablespoons of salt.
Let soak overnight.
In morning, drain and rinse off.
Put in large kettle.
Add all ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour and put in jars. Really good.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco, vanilla and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt, alternating with milk.
Add nuts.
Spray Pam in pan.
Bake at 350° for at least 60 minutes.
Should make at least 2 loaves.
Let cool and wrap in foil.

title: benedictine spread
directions: Combine all ingredients with 1 to 2 drops of food coloring in blender or food processor.
Add more color if needed.
Blend until smooth.
Makes filling for 6 to 8 full size sandwiches.

title: old fashioned sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream together sugar and shortening; add eggs and lemon extract.
Blend and add sour cream. Combine this mixture with sifted dry ingredients.
Mixture will be stiff.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs until thick and frothy;
beat in sugar.
Melt chocolate and shortening together over slow heat.
Add to first mixture.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
For better results sift these together.
Add the flour mixture to the first mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
To prepare the 8 x 12 pan, grease well and line with wax paper.
Then grease the waxed paper. Spread into pan
and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares and let cool in pan.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute until tender onions in oleo on low heat.
Add chicken soup, cheese, milk, broccoli and rice.
Mix all together, then pour into greased baking dish.
Top with a little grated cheese. Bake in 300° to 325° oven until bubbly hot.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Use large saucepan to combine and cook all ingredients. Combine cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and butter.
Then bring to a rolling boil and cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Let the peanut butter melt and then add oats. Mix oats well and drop spoonfuls on a piece of wax paper to cool. Then serve.

title: quick rolls
directions: In a large bowl mix the ingredients in given order.
Spray a muffin tin with nonstick vegetable spray.
Fill each cup 2/3 full of mix.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: pineapple raisin muffins
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Beat in egg, juice and orange peel.
Combine remaining ingredients; stirring until blended.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: camp beans
directions: Soak beans in water to cover in soup pot overnight.
Drain; rinse.
Add water to cover, onion, garlic, bay leaves and chicken bouillon.
Simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, seasonings, ham chunks and brown sugar.
Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup of water to a boil, then add 2 cups of sugar and 1 cup of white syrup.
Stir until dissolved and boil until it will spin a thread.
Now add 2 cups of raw peanuts and cook slowly over a low fire until it turns a golden brown.
Take from fire and add 2 tablespoons of baking soda and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Stir quickly.
Spread on two large, well buttered cookie sheets.
Place in cold area.

title: party size fudgy pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine baking mix and cocoa.
Stir in 2 cups of sweetened condensed milk, 1/2 cup syrup and vanilla until blended. Spoon evenly into prepared pan.
In a small bowl, combine rest of milk, rest of syrup and hot water.
Pour liquid mixture carefully over top of mixture in pan.
Do not stir.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set and cake begins to pull away from sides of pan. Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dish, spooning pudding from bottom of pan over top.
Serve warm.
Garnish with whipped topping or ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: easy hershey fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until boiling; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool for 10 seconds.
Add the chocolate bars.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into a 10 x 13-inch greased glass container.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter before baking at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out half the pastry and line a 9-inch pie plate.
Place crackers in crust.
In saucepan over high heat, bring water, sugar and cream of tartar to boil; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind; cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot with spread. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll out remaining pastry; place over pie. Trim, seal and flute edges.
Slit top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden.
Cool completely.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well and shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: Saute beef, onions, green pepper and garlic until tender. Add tomato paste, water and salt. Mix well.
Add beans and mushrooms.
Simmer until all ingredients are thoroughly heated. Pour into baking dish and cover with canned biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden.

title: mom's chicken fricassee
directions: Take 2 tablespoons oil in large frying pan.
Cut up large onions small.
Put in large frying pan on medium heat until onions are a bit soft.
Take parts of chicken and put salt and paprika on each piece.
Put skin side down on onions.
Lower to simmer and cook until tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut chipped beef up small (use scissors or sharp knife). Combine all ingredients; roll in chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to eat!

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in half carefully; do not puncture bottom. Squeeze out some seeds and the juice.
Add mixture of bread crumbs, cheese, oregano, salt and pepper and a few drops of oil to each tomato half.
Put under broiler for 3 to 6 minutes.

title: sky high strawberry pie
directions: In a large bowl, mash enough berries to equal 3 cups.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in the mashed berries and water; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat; add food coloring if desired.
Pour into a large bowl. Chill for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is just slightly warm.
Fold in the remaining berries.
Pile into pie shell.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: bacon fat cookies
directions: Mix bacon fat, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs until creamy. Add dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts.
Divide and mold into 2 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill until stiff.
Slice and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: firecracker casserole
directions: Cook the meat in skillet until it is no longer pink, drain. Add beans, chili pwd., cumin and salt.
Transfer to a 9 by 13 in. baking dish.
Arrange tortillas over the top; combine soup and tomatoes, then pour over the tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 25-30 min. Yields 8 servings.

title: decorator icing
directions: Mix together.
Yields enough icing to do flowers and leaves for 350+ cake squares.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Mix with spinach.
Cut out center of bread.
Break into small pieces. Arrange pieces of bread around dip.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and
eggs.
Make
a
paste with food coloring and cocoa and add
to
mixture.
Add
salt
and flour with buttermilk and
vanilla.
Alternately
add soda and vinegar (mix vinegar and soda together); don't beat hard, just blend. Bake 30 minutes, at 350°,
in
two
8-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Frost with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all of above ingredients with a mixer and serve with chips.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook until 270° or brittle ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir and mix. Shape corn into balls and place on wax paper.

title: fruited cabbage salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and set aside.
In a jar with a tight fitting lid, combine the mayonnaise, milk, sugar, lemon juice; shake well.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss to coat.

title: mignonette of beef
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except beef and vegetables, then add the beef, cut into 1 1/2 to 2-inch cubes.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours or overnight.
Alternate meat and vegetables of your choice on skewer.
Broil about 20 minutes, brushing with sauce occasionally.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Have
all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift flour, baking powder
and salt.
Cream butter and sugar until silvery and light. Add
eggs,
one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine milk and vanilla, then add to cream mixture alternately with flour mixture.
Be sure to begin and end with dry ingredients.
Beat	only
enough
to blend.
Fold in nuts. Spoon batter
into
greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.	Bake at 350° for
to
60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Rub inside of fondue pot or saucepan with cut edge of garlic, then discard.
In fondue pot, simmer apple juice.
Blend in soup. Combine cheese and cornstarch; stir into soup mixture.
Heat until cheese melts; stir now and then.
Spear bread with fondue fork and dip into fondue.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour.
Stir in milk, salt and chicken broth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix chicken and noodles with sauce.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until top is lightly browned.

title: one dish ham bake(chicken, turkey or beef can be used.)
directions: Mix broccoli, soups, 1 cup milk, meat and onion.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Bisquick and 1 1/2 cups milk and pour evenly over soup mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 450° oven.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with tossed salad and French bread for complete meal.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and beat well. Add baking powder to flour.
Add alternately with milk to batter. Add vanilla and mix well.
Makes 3 or 4 layers.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Use favorite filling and icing.

title: jewel cookies
directions: In medium bowl with wooden spoon, beat butter, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour just until combined. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 375°.
Using hands, roll dough into balls 1-inch in diameter; dip in egg white, then roll in walnuts.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
With thimble or thumb, press center of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until a delicate golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool.
Place 1/4 teaspoon jelly in center of each cookie.

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, soda and corn syrup; cook until it forms soft ball in water; remove.
Add vanilla, butter, salt and nuts; beat until stiff.
Hurry and drop by spoonfuls onto oiled waxed paper. If cooked too much, add a little water to soften.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil giblets in salted water with bay leaf and beef bouillon cubes.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Saute green pepper, onion and celery in saucepan with a little butter.
Chop cooked giblets after they cook and cool a little.
Add giblets, ground beef and sauteed vegetables to rice.
Add a teaspoon of poultry seasoning and 1/2 teaspoon sage to rice mixture.
Cover and cook until rice is done. Serve with baked chicken.

title: curried pears
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use a small baking dish.
Peel, half and core pears.
Combine butter, brown sugar, curry powder and salt; mix with a spoon.
Cook 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jake kalberer's spinach dip
directions: Put all ingredients together (except rye bread) in food processor or blender.
Hollow out bread; save extra bread for dipping.
Pour dip into hollowed out rye bread.

title: microwave tomato jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart glass measure or microproof bowl.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes on High, or until cheese is melted, stirring once during cooking time.
Blend thoroughly with electric mixer.
Pour into serving bowl.
Serve with corn chips or dipping-style potato chips or raw, fresh vegetables.
Makes about 4 cups.
Total cooking time: 5 to 7 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a small skillet, melt margarine and saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms, stirring often, until tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir together with next 6 items.
Add noodles, mixing well.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg yolks; add condensed milk and lime juice and beat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: streusel-filled coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together and stir 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
The mixture for the struedel is the brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and butter.
Spread half batter mixture in greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 streusel mixture.
Alternate rest.
Bake in greased and floured pan 25 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Double batter for 13 x 11 x 2-inch pan.

title: cherry pie bars
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Makes soft dough (sticky).
Spread 3/4 (plus) of dough on greased sheet cake pan, will seem thin (don't have bare spots).
Spread on pie cherries (get red everywhere).
Take a little at a time part of the 1/4 dough left; add flour and pat out real thin between hands.
Place patchy over cherries.
Looks real messy, cherries and red can show.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (when it starts to brown and is firm, just barely brown).

title: apple-pecan caramel salad
directions: Combine apples and pecans in bowl.
Mix yogurt, light mayonnaise, sugar substitute and cinnamon together and pour mixture over apples.
Toss gently to coat.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: mrs. lynch's old country cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with 2 knives.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in raisins and seed.
Add milk; stir.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan (or use cooking oil spray).
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Can also use 3 small 6-inch round pans and bake for 35 minutes.

title: pesto chicken linguine
directions: For pesto sauce, in blender or food processor container, combine spinach, parsley, chicken broth, egg yolk, Parmesan cheese, basil and garlic.
Cover and blend until mixture is pureed.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Keep hot.

title: steak in a bag
directions: You can roast the steak in dry heat in the oven, if you desire.
Roast at 375° for 40 minutes.
Wipe steak dry.
Combine butter, garlic, oil, salt and pepper.
Spread butter mixture on both sides of steak.
Press crumbs firmly onto steak on both sides.
Place in brown grocery type bag.
Close with paper clips. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Slide onto carving board.
Carve into 1/4-inch diagonal slices to serve.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs; cool and remove shells.
Cut in half.
Remove yolks to mixing bowl.
With fork, crumble yolks for easy mixing.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, green relish and mayonnaise and mix well.
Do not use too much mayonnaise or mixture will be runny.
Put 1/2 tablespoon of the yolk mixture back in egg white.
Garnish with paprika.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill.

title: strawberry puff
directions: Blend all ingredients. Beat 2 minutes. Wash and stem berries and put in 8-inch square glass pan. Spoon mixture over berries. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Double recipe for 9 x 13 pan. (Substitute raspberries, blueberries, crushed pineapple or apples can be used.)

title: cheese olive balls
directions: Blend cheese and margarine (room temperature).
Add flour and other ingredients.
Pinch off dough and form into balls around olives.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients.
Boil 7 1/2 minutes or until it makes a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and marshmallows.
Add vanilla.
Do not use a mixer!
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Add nuts and pour into well buttered pan.
Let cool at least 4 to 6 hours.
Do not cut until cooled.

title: quick and hearty soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat. Cut up tomatoes slightly.
Add beef, along with mixed vegetables, water, onion soup mix, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni, then lower heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Pat in pan. Melt chocolate chips in
microwave and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Cool.

title: parmesan round steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 servings.
Pound each to 1/2-inch thickness. Combine egg and milk.
Mix bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Dip steaks into egg mixture.
Dredge with seasoned crumbs.
Brown meat in oil.
Add water.
Sprinkle oregano on steaks.
Place 2 teaspoons Parmesan cheese on each steak.
Combine salt and paprika.
Sprinkle onions with salt mixture; add to meat.
Cover tightly.
Cook in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces and mix with nuts and coconut. Combine flour, baking powder and soda.
Add fruit.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Pour over fruit mixture and mix well.
Bake in 2 greased tube pans at 250° for 3 hours.
Yields 10 pounds. (Use a dishpan to mix fruit and flour and pour egg mixture over it.
Makes a big mixture.)

title: wiener schnitzel
directions: Sprinkle veal with lemon juice, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Then roll in flour, egg and breadcrumbs.
Fry on one side in hot butter.
Turn.
Reduce heat. Place cheese slice on each cutlet.
Slowly fry other side.
Serve with crisp salad.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: When chicken is cool, break into small pieces.
Store each of the first 3 ingredients in a Ziploc bag until ready to use.
In a skillet, brown the sesame seed, almonds and ginger.
Store in Ziploc bag until ready to use.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Heat a wok or large pot until hot.
Add a small amount of oil to coat bottom.
When oil is hot, add cabbage, onion and celery and stir-fry until it is about half done.
Add sausage rings and continue stirring over high heat until sausage is heated through. Add V-8 juice, beef broth, soy sauce and pepper.
Cook until heated.
Thicken with cornstarch and a little of the reserved beef broth.
Heat through.
Add sesame oil just before serving.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add rice and broccoli.
Heat soup in double boiler.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Stir into broccoli.

title: easy deviled eggs
directions: Mix yolks of hard-boiled eggs with Thousand Island dressing to desired consistency.
Stuff eggs.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into 6 oval patties.
In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook patties until browned. Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms.
Return patties to skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning patties occasionally.

title: lemon chiffon pudding
directions: Cream
butter,
sugar
and
flour
together and add egg yolks, lemon
juice and milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Place
in
pan of warm water and bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until firm.
Serves 8.

title: gr. aunt frances' celery sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and squeeze seeds out of them.
Mix all ingredients together and boil.
Seal while hot.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; let egg whites warm to room temperature.
Beat yolks with shortening until well blended.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add on low speed and beat in flour alternately with milk.
Add coconut and blend well. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "berry" delicious fruit shortcake
directions: Combine
flour,
baking
powder,
salt	and
sugar. Add combined
milk,
melted margarine and beaten egg, mixing until well
moistened.
Spread
into greased and floured 8-inch cake pan. Bake
at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer in loaf pan in order given.
Do not mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place the chicken in a glass baking dish.
Make the rice according to the directions on the box.
Add the 2 cans of soup and 1 can of water.
Pour the rice-soup mixture over the chicken and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Add the cooking sherry and bake approximately 1/2 hour longer.

title: korean fried rice(bokgeum bahb)
directions: Separate cold rice grains with a knife or chopsticks.
Chop ham into small pieces.
Rinse frozen green peas under cold water and set aside.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in frypan and make Egg Pancakes.*
Chop Egg Pancakes into thin strips and set aside.

title: corn dog twists
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat or in microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds.
Unroll dough into 1 long sheet.
Seal the short center perforation.
Separate into 8 long strips.
Wrap each strip around 1 hot dog.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush each corn dog twist with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 16 minutes or until dough is light brown.

title: fudge fruit and cream salad
directions: Mix
pudding and buttermilk.
Fold in
whipping
cream. Break up cookies and fold into salad.
Add oranges and pineapple. Chill.

title: beer nuts
directions: Boil on medium heat 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir once or more to keep from burning.
Boil until dry.
Heat oven 300°, grease jelly roll pan and spread nuts in pan.
Sprinkle coarse salt on nuts. Bake 20 minutes.
Stir and salt again.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Stir so won't stick.
Cool and store in container.

title: cherry charlies
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar, salt, milk and corn syrup on medium heat for 2 minutes.
Stir in other ingredients.
Shape into small balls and drop onto wax paper.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: skillet or wok lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook lasagna or noodles in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or just until tender.
Drain lasagna noodles and set aside.
Preheat wok or large skillet over high heat. Break up meat.
Stir-fry meat and garlic for 2 to 3 minutes or until meat is brown.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and cooked noodles.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Beat eggs in a medium bowl. Add milk and vegetable soup mix. Squeeze water out of the spinach.
Add to other ingredients.
Add the cheese; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: gloop(gloop can be pulled to and fro for a snap-and-crackly tug-of-war!)
directions: Pour the white glue into a clean, empty peanut butter jar. Add 1/2 cup of water and 10 drops of food coloring and stir. Combine the Borax and a cup of water in a medium size plastic bowl.
Slowly pour the glue mixture into the Borax solution and stir until well mixed.
The Borax causes the mixture to congeal. Scoop the gloop out of the water and knead it in your hands until it becomes dry enough to play with.
If stored in a sealed container or plastic bag, it should keep for several weeks.
Gloop dries out after a lot of handling.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix altogether.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 8 to 9-inch greased square pan for very thick pieces or larger pan for more servings!

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and pour into hot skillet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be made into muffins, also.

title: cheerio bars
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in saucepan; cook over low heat until it comes to a full boil.
Stir in the peanut butter; stir until melted in.
Add rest of ingredients; stir until well coated. Press into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: chocolate creams
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Blend in sugar, cream and vanilla.
Chill about 30 minutes.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls and roll in nuts.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: double cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger, crumbs, onion, pepper, egg, Italian seasoning and 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
On a sheet of tinfoil, spread mixture into a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with cheeses and roll into a log.
Seal ends and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
At the end of the hour, pour remaining tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: For Cake:
Cream sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Then stir into first mixture, alternately with flour and salt.
Add peaches and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: good rice
directions: Mix all together in casserole.
Place margarine on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: baked lamb chop casserole
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place in greased casserole.
Pour drippings over meat.
Saute onion in butter until golden brown. Mix onion, potatoes, cucumbers, salt and pepper.
Spread over chops.
Add tomatoes.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 2 hours.

title: cool vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Put in large bowl.
Mix together and add dressing.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Stir and ready to serve.
Serves approximately 10 people.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend and beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased pan at 325° for 60 minutes. Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla into margarine. Blend into eggs. Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cook meat, onion and pepper in oil until browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Simmer for 45 minutes or 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: garbage cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir all ingredients into large bowl in order given.
(Butter should be soft.)
Mix by hand, then beat on medium speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes until a toothpick comes out dry.
Cool, then top with cream cheese frosting.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together.
Fold in 1 (8 ounce) container of Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell and chill.
Sprinkle coconut on top (optional).

title: buttermilk meat loaf ring
directions: Combine buttermilk, bread, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly, just until blended.
Pack firmly into buttered ring mold. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Allow to stand
for 5 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Turn out onto serving dish and drizzle catsup over meat loaf.

title: sweet potato slaw
directions: Combine vegetables in a bowl. Toss gently. Combine remaining ingredients and stir well. Add to cabbage mixture. Toss well. Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings.
Serving Size:
1/2 cup. Exchanges:
1 bread/starch.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease again.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans onto paper.

title: refrigerated cheese torte
directions: Save 1/2 cup of this mixture for top.
Blend ingredients as for pie crust.
Grease 9 x 3-inch loose bottom torte pan and line sides and bottom with graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool before freezing.

title: geneva's coffee bars
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the shortening and sugar. Add the eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add the hot coffee.
Mix well. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon. Stir into the egg mixture, blending well.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While still warm, frost with a powdered sugar glaze.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and mix until well blended.
Add the eggs and beat thoroughly.
Mix soda, salt and cinnamon with flour. Add to first mixture alternately with the milk.
Fold in rolled oats, nutmeats and raisins.
Drop from spoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake 10 minutes in a hot oven (400°).

title: berried delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: italian beef
directions: Bake in a heavy Dutch oven for 3 1/2 hours at 325°.
The last 30 minutes, cut strings.
Serve on sub buns.

title: seasoned black-eyed peas
directions: Drain peas (if desired, instead of soaking, cover peas with water and bring to boil then let stand 1 hour).
Combine peas, water, bouillon, onion, pepper, garlic, thyme, vegetable oil and salt in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and cover.
Simmer gently for 1 hour or until tender.
Add additional water if pea mixture becomes too thick.
Serves 8.

title: noodle-pineapple kugel
directions: Nadine Shirley, one of the volunteers known as Apple Pandowdies, passed away before last Apple Jubilee in Waverly, Missouri.
Her daughter, Pat Maycock, continues Nadine's tradition of baking apple dumplings for the celebration, using local Jonathan apples.
Baking powder lightens the flaky pastry.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and milk in saucepan.
Heat until smooth and very warm.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and egg yolks.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, turn heat to 350° and bake 10 more minutes.
Prepare Never Fail Meringue while pie bakes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling in order given.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie filling comes out clean.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: brunch souffle
directions: In a large casserole greased with margarine, break up bread. Grate Cheddar cheese and mix with bread.
In a blender, mix quickly eggs and milk.
Pour over bread and cheese mixture.
Cover with foil and let sit in fridge overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; 35 to 40 minutes covered, 20 to 25 minutes uncovered.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Cut in Crisco until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Stir in buttermilk. Knead dough gently.
Roll out to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter and place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 450 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar; beat again. Add 1/2 cup more sugar and vanilla.
Take 24 Ritz crackers and crush into mixture.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion rings
directions: Peel onion. Cut in 1/2-inch slices. Separate rings.
Combine dry ingredients and stir well. Add eggs, milk and teaspoon oil. Beat until smooth. Dip onion rings into batter and fry in deep hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crisp marshmallow bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring occasionally until marshmallows are melted.
Remove from heat; blend in vanilla.
In a large bowl, add mixture to cereal.
Stir to coat.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal mix, eggs, buttermilk and corn. Saute ground beef; add onion and cook until onion is transparent, then drain. Pour 1/2 of the cornbread mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased liberally. Crumble ground beef over cornbread mix and sprinkle cheese over this. Top with peppers, then rest of the cornbread mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pickle and onion salad
directions: Cut into chunks the onions and pickles.
Mix with mayonnaise to make sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with fried fish.

title: baked eggplant parmesiana
directions: Dip each slice of eggplant into well beaten egg and into seasoned bread crumbs.
Fry breaded eggplant slices in medium to hot oil in frying pan, 2 minutes on each side.
Drain cooked eggplant slices on paper towels.
Layer in glass baking dish some of your favorite tomato sauce, then all of the cooked eggplant. Top with more sauce and finish by topping with some grated Mozzarella cheese and dried oregano.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic food bag or bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss until potatoes are coated evenly. Place into shallow baking or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped fresh parsley.
Per serving:
174 calories, 9 grams fat.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour, stirring until smooth and thick.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Stir in all of the remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Add top crust.
Make several slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mashed potato candy
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to cold potato.
Roll with rolling pin dusted with flour.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a pinwheel; place in refrigerator.
Cut into slices.
May be frozen. Wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap so it doesn't dry out.

title: chocolate boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa over medium heat until it comes to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: vegetarian four-bean chili(low-calorie, low-fat, low-cholesterol)
directions: Heat oil in large pot over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute 4 minutes or until onion is softened. Add carrot; cover and cook 2 minutes.
Add zucchini, summer squash, chili powder, oregano and cumin.
Saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes breaking up with wooden spoon the beer and salt.
Bring to boiling. Lower heat; simmer, partially covered 15 minutes. Stir in all the beans.
Simmer, stirring, until heated through.

title: rye snacks
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Spread on bread slices and place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight or until ready to use. Serve with veggies or chips.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, mix beef broth with cornstarch and teriyaki sauce; set aside.
In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over high heat; add mushrooms, green pepper and onions.
Stir-fry until tender.
Remove to bowl.
Add remaining oil and beef; stir-fry until cooked.
Add beef broth mixture and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add vegetables.
Serve in warm pastry shells.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Simmer peeled, sliced apples in undiluted apple juice until apples are tender.
Add cinnamon and cornstarch moistened with a small amount of water.
Cook until thickened.

title: meringue cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix in order given.
Pour into 2 layer cake pans.

title: biscotti
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Slice and rebake on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken jerusalem
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour and lightly brown in oil.
Place in casserole with mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Stir in garlic and spices (with tomatoes). Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender, adding sherry during last few minutes of cooking time. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients: flour, sugar, pumpkin pie spice, soda, powder and salt in one bowl.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash, stem and	quarter apples.
Place cider in kettle. Add apples and	cook
slowly
until
soft.
Put apples through strainer.
Measure apples and for each cup, add 1/2 cup sugar. Mix well.
Add	spices.
Cook
slowly
over low heat, stirring until sugar is
dissolved,
then	cook rapidly until butter is thick.

title: mississippi pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together for two minutes.
Pour slowly over eggs and stir well.
Add margarine, vanilla and nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: easy, good salad
directions: In a bowl, mix together cottage cheese, Cool Whip and jello. Drain fruit and blend in. Chill before serving.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain.
Add can of beans and taco seasoning.
Stuff tortillas and place in casserole dish.
Mix chili and picante sauce in separate bowl.
Pour over tortillas. Top with cheese and bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in casserole.
Top with crackers, crumbled and 1 stick margarine, mixed.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: barbecued steak platter(cube steaks)
directions: Combine all ingredients, heat and pour over 4 cube steaks. Let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain and place steaks on rack 2 inches below broiler.
Broil 5 minutes on each side, basting once or twice with sauce.
Brown 4 bread slices in butter or margarine and arrange steaks on slices.
Serve with onion and pickle.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar together.
Add Jell-O; when dissolved, add cup water.
Refrigerate until almost jelled; add cheese, Cool Whip and nuts.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes well and chop.
Grate cheese.
Combine with mayonnaise and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: cocoa fudge icing
directions: Combine all except vanilla in pot.
Slowly bring to a boil. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take from heat; add vanilla and beat until spreading consistency.
Ready to frost 2 or 3 layer cake.
(I usually use Pillsbury Plus yellow cake mix for layers.)

title: italian supper casserole
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles according to directions.
Drain rinse and separate.
brown the beef and sprinkle the mix over the meat.
Add tomatoes and blend well.
Whip the cream cheese. In a buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Make 2 layers each of noodles, meat & dollops of cream cheese. Bake at 350 degree for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese goulash
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add onion and celery and continue cooking until tender, but not soft.
Add bean sprouts and soup. Heat thoroughly.
Add canned mushrooms if desired.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef.
While beef is cooking, cook all other ingredients together. Drain beef, then mix all together in a large pot. Cook for 10 more minutes. Very good!

title: pizza crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt. Gradually add water and 2 tablespoons peanut oil to flour mixture. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Roll dough to a 12-inch circle; place on a greased pizza pan. Form a standing rim on crust. Prick dough with fork
randomly. Let rest 10 minutes. Prebake at 450° for 5 minutes.

title: cajun turkey
directions: Mix together m.s.g., cayenne pepper, paprika, white pepper and celery salt.
Rub into turkey cavity and all over the skin.
(Be careful and don't touch your hands to your eyes!)
Separate garlic bud and clean cloves.
Slit holes all over turkey and insert cloves.
Also place cloves of garlic in stomach cavity of turkey. Mix a 4 ounce bottle of shrimp and crab boil with 4 (4 ounce) bottles of water and inject into turkey all over the body.
Place turkey in stainless steel roasting pan and cover with foil. Refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours, occasionally basting with juices in pan.
When ready to cook, heat oil.
Place whole turkey in oil and fry until tender.

title: satsuma salad
directions: Peel the satsumas and cut crosswise into slices.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over satsuma slices.
Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight (or at least 3 to 4 hours).
To serve, spoon mixture onto lettuce leaves.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat together all ingredients except bananas.
Then mix well. Turn in bananas.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix together peas, onions, soup, bacon and water chestnuts. Place in casserole dish. Top with Stove Top mix and melted butter. Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: heavenly fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill in a classy glass bowl.

title: lite meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape in 7 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan which was coated with cooking spray (Pam).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 6. Pepper slices can be placed on top of meat loaf before cooking for decoration.

title: chicken aspic salad
directions: Sprinkle 1 envelope gelatin in tomato juice.
Heat, stirring, until dissolved.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and dash of Tabasco.
Set aside to cool.
In separate saucepan, sprinkle 1 envelope gelatin in chicken stock.
Heat; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Let cool.
Add chicken, celery and green pepper.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into loaf pan that has been Pam coated.
Chill.
When firm, add tomato aspic mixture.
When aspic is almost firm, spread last half of chicken mix.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: rigatoni casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook spaghetti sauce.
Add mix and water.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Layer all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Remove from heat.
Add 1 box powdered sugar.
Beat.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Spread on cake as soon as it is taken from the oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake for 9 to 11 minutes, until golden brown.
Yields 5 dozen cookies (using tablespoons of dough).

title: james earl jones' chilean sea bass
directions: Slice and cook onions in a skillet on low heat until caramelized (between 1 and 2 hours).

Puree all ingredients except olive oil and chicken broth. Heat olive oil. Add ingredients and cook on low for 30 minutes. Add chicken broth as necessary. Season bass with salt and white pepper to taste.
Cover bass with onions and bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Each of 6 servings should include one piece of bass over about 1/6 of the sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, syrup and margarine.
Add salt, vanilla and eggs (one at a time).
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: smoky salmon appetizer ball
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Place mixture on plastic wrap and form into a ball.
Cover and chill overnight.
Several hours before serving, roll in chopped nuts. Chill until ready to serve.

title: japanese fruit pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Bake at 300° for 55 minutes.
Do not bake crust before pouring in the ingredients.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, pepper, salt and soup.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine and shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Press into center of hot cookies, 36 chocolate kisses.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Mix all together by hand until all ingredients are combined. Put in dish and put in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with ketchup. Cook uncovered.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash and cut cucumbers in half lengthwise; pack in hot jars with the last 5 ingredients put in each pint jar.
Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Tie pickling spices in a cheesecloth bag; add to vinegar mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Heat to boiling and pour over cucumbers; leave 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps. Process pints and quarts 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield: about 7 pints.

title: orange molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet and place in refrigerator until partly set (watch carefully).
Add other ingredients and fold in Cool Whip last.
Chill and enjoy.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chili sauce, shrimp and parsley. Spread on plate.
Cover with chili sauce, then sprinkle tiny shrimp and parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: aunt beta's beer bread
directions: Blend beer, egg and sugar, then add flour.
Put it in a bread pan and cover with towel.
It rises in an hour or so.
Bake at 350° for an hour.
Cool and slice bread.
Spread real butter on top.
Mmmm!
Good!

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and drain, then add seasoning mix, taco sauce and kidney beans.
Let all this get hot, then its ready to eat.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon 1 teaspoon filling into pastry shell.
Bake tarts at 350° for 17 minutes. Garnish with cream.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the egg and vanilla. Then the rest of the ingredients.
Roll in balls and flatten. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Combine ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop walnuts.
Beat eggs; gradually beat in sugar, then oil. Combine first mixture, alternating with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla extract.
Turn into 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° or until loaves test done, approximately 1 hour.
(Bake on lowest rack in oven.)
Let stand about 10 minutes, turn out onto wire racks to cool.
If desired, loaves may be lightly frosted with confectioners sugar, butter and vanilla mixed to a spreading consistency with milk. Makes two loaves.
Freezes well!

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions until clear.
Pour onions into a prepared pie shell.
Add grated cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk and pour over cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni-beef skillet supper
directions: Cook the macaroni in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain and set
aside.
Saute
the meat, onion and garlic in oil until the
meat
loses
its
pink
color and the onions are tender.
Add
salt,
pepper,
tomato sauce, catsup, mushrooms, Worcestershire
sauce and Italian seasoning.
Bring mixture to a boil and
then simmer gently for about 5 minutes. Mix in the cooked
macaroni and simmer 5 more minutes.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 270 calories per serving.

title: artichoke and spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Saute onion in butter.
Mix spinach, onion, artichoke hearts, sour cream and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese in a casserole dish.
Add pepper and toss well.
Put remaining 1/4 cup cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: delicious cabbage
directions: Brown onions.
Remove from pan.
Place 1/3 cabbage in pan followed by 1/2 of bell pepper, one tomato and half the browned onion.
Layer with another 1/3 of cabbage and remaining bell pepper, tomato and onions.
Sprinkle remaining cabbage on top and add salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until limp.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add cooked meat, if desired.

title: coconut grouper
directions: Combine lime juice, oregano and half the garlic.
Marinate the fish in this for at least 1/2 hour.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Dissolve 1 pint of lime in 2 gallons of water.
Peel, seed and cut cucumbers into strips.
(Use large cucumbers, even the white ones; use the meat only.
You can fix small ones the same way.) Pour lime mixture over cucumbers and let stand for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse cucumbers.
Fill with ice cold water and let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices together.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Put on stove next morning and boil for 35 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in olive oil with garlic, basil, parsley and salt. Add tomatoes and paste.
Simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles until tender (rinse with cold water).
In bowl, combining cottage cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put little meat on bottom, then noodles, half of cottage cheese mixture, half of Mozzarella cheese, half of meat.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: meatballs with gravy
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients; shape into balls.
Brown in the shortening.
Mix the soup with water; pour over meatballs. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Combine rhubarb, apples and strawberries; spoon into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over fruit.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in brown sugar and oats.
Sprinkle over rhubarb mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve cold or warm with a scoop of ice cream if desired.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and clean peppers.
Parboil peppers for 5 minutes.
Let cool and drain.
Combine rice, meat, salt, pepper and butter; mix well.
Stuff peppers; place peppers in a pan, uncovered, with a little water in the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (check after 45 minutes).
Heat can of tomato sauce and serve with peppers.

title: barbecue coleslaw
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat just until sugar dissolves.
Stir in barbecue sauce, water, mayonnaise, mustard powder and red pepper seasoning.
Combine cabbage and carrots in large bowl.
Pour dressing over; toss to combine.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients but potatoes and mix well.
Add potatoes and mix gently.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This
can be frozen and taken out when needed.

title: garlic spread
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Slice about 1/2-inch off the top of the garlic. Wrap it in aluminum foil and bake for 35 minutes. Remove foil and press until all flesh squeezes out. You should have 1 heaping tablespoonful of puree. Mix it with the yogurt, parsley, black pepper and salt.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Melt butter; stir in Eagle Brand milk and Hershey's syrup. For the cake just bake devil's food cake and follow directions on box.
Cut cake and ice cream in squares and pour fudge over top.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions without adding fat or salt.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Set aside.
In a large bowl combine tomato sauce, dressing , basil, and oregano.
Add tomatoes, cucumber, onion, and olives.
Stir until coated.
Add pasta and gently toss.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Bake in Magnolite pot.
Pour in cherry filling.
Layer can of crushed pineapple on top of cherry filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of fillings.
Sprinkle pecans over mixture.
Pour melted margarine over mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Then turn oven down to 350° and bake for 25 more minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased iron skillet on 400° to 425° until brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan and 2-quart saucepan.

title: sea scallops with lemon butter sauce
directions: Coat 1 lb. sea scallops in flour. Season with salt and pepper. Saute scallops in olive oil & butter in a large skillet over high heat for 2 minutes on each side.	Remove scallops.
Add butter, lemon juice, parsley, salt & pepper and heat.
Serve scallops over rice and top with sauce from skillet.

title: papa nick's dill pickles
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to boil; let stand 20 minutes. When cool, pour over cukes and green tomatoes, prepared according to preference.
Small tomatoes and cucumbers can be left whole, if desired, and larger vegetables can be cut into chunks.
Cucumbers may be sliced open lengthwise and cut into quarters or eighths. Put vegetables in quart jars; to each jar, add 2 sprigs dill and 2 large garlic cloves, depending on taste.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Season and cook chicken.
Bone and cut in bite-size pieces. Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and heat.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crackers and poppy seed and place on top of meat.
Drizzle melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cut strawberries in half.
Slice bananas.
Drain pineapple. Cream sugar and cheese together.
Fold in tub of Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix together the frozen strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Add to cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Butter pan.
Cover pan with frozen bread dough, then add pudding mix, brown sugar, cinnamon, pecans and butter.
Cover; let sit out on counter overnight.
Cook at 350° for 15 minutes uncovered, then 15 minutes covered.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and Miracle Whip and whip the cream in separate bowl.
Fold crushed pineapple, marshmallows and chopped cherries into cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Last, add whipped cream.
Put into 13 x 9-inch dish; freeze overnight.
Let set at room temperature 1/2 hour before eating.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12 3/4-inch oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in bottom rack of oven.

title: quick fruit cake
directions: Combine all these ingredients. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Makes about a 3 pound fruit cake.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown beef, onions, pepper and mushrooms.
Add tomato paste, sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Arrange in 2 small or one large oblong dish.

title: apple snack
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place apples in a single layer in a large, flat baking pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, and stir in popcorn and pecans. Mix remaining ingredients in a cup and drizzle over apples, popcorn, and pecans. Return to oven, and bake for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of red coloring and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk, alternating with sifted flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
In small cup, mix soda and vinegar, then add to rest of mixture, blending instead of beating. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, juice and sugar in a gallon jug.
Add water to fill jug.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and serve with Triscuits.

title: miracle brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Add shortening, eggs, vanilla and corn syrup.
Mix for 2 minutes at low speed; scrape bowl.
Stir in nuts; save some nuts to sprinkle on top.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
Combine curry, yogurt, mayonnaise, lemon juice, mustard and garlic.
Add chicken, red pepper, celery, scallions and sunflower seed.
Toss lightly. Spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons into each shell.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: choc' gravy
directions: Mix well and cook over medium heat until thick.
Serve over buttered toast or biscuits.

title: party mints
directions: Mix
with
fork until moist.
Add milk.
Do not get too moist. Mix with hands.
Will be very stiff.
Push into rubber molds.

title: joe's cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients, except sour cream.
Beat until smooth, blending in sour cream.
Pour into graham or nut crust, trim with reserved crumbs.
Bake in moderate (375°) oven for 35 minutes or until just set.
Let cool with oven door open.
Do not overheat or cool too rapidly.
Chill well.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions into thin rings.
Saute in margarine until limp or opaque.
Pour half of onions into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with Parmesan cheese, then crushed crackers.
Repeat layers and bake, uncovered, in 325° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Delicious with steak!!

title: peach cobbler cake
directions: Pour undrained peaches in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Jell-O over peaches.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Poke holes in cake mix and pour 1 1/2 cups water over all.
Dot with 1 1/4 sticks butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Combine ingredients, except beef.
Mix well. Add ground beef; mix.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Drain; let stand for 5 minutes.

title: linda's strawberry salad
directions: Mix jell-O with hot water.
Add pineapple with the juice and the pie filling; mix well.
Place in a 13 x 9 casserole dish.
Let congeal in refrigerator.
In a small bowl mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Pour this mixture over congealed salad.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine chocolate cake mix, butter, water, oil and 1/2 can sweetened condensed milk in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, buttermilk, eggs, blackberry jam and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat well on low speed.
Add combined ingredients and beat on medium speed to blend well.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans for 40 minutes or until tests done.
Cool completely and frost with Buttermilk Icing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together with your hands.
Make into small balls and bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for about 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve hot.
These make such a hit with every one and are so easy.

title: polka dot cake
directions: Mix dates and hot water.
Let cool.
Cream butter and sugar, then beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture. Add dates, vanilla and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread batter in greased pan.
Top with remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in a covered container.
When ready to serve, let defrost to a slushy consistency.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce in pan. Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Add orange juice and pineapple. Stir until smooth. Pour into mold and chill.

title: orange balls
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Roll in chopped pecans or coconut, if desired.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cup cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Press flat.
Bake at 325° for approximately eight minutes. Watch carefully for these goodies burn easily.

title: pa's fruit bread
directions: Mix sugar, cooking oil and eggs.
Add fruit and nuts; mix well.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt oleo in dish.
Combine all other ingredients and mix lightly.
Add to butter and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vegetable oil, mashed bananas and vanilla. Then add sifted flour with baking soda and salt.
Add nuts if you like.
Pour mixture into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Arrange cut cookie dough (1/8 to 1/4-inch) rounds in slightly overlapping pattern on pizza pan. Press dough together to seal.
Bake until puffed and golden, about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in tightly covered container.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons mixture in cup of hot water.

title: sugar pie
directions: Mix the flour with the sugar.
Add the milk.
Mix and pour into 1 pie crust and cover with the second crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Lower the heat to 300 degrees, and bake for approximately 15 minutes longer.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with sauce.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Place pastry in pie pan.
Arrange rhubarb.
Mix sugar with flour and add beaten egg yolks and butter.
Spoon mixture over rhubarb.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 12 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 25 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets until done.
Peel while still hot; let cool.
Slice in thin round slices.
Mix in mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Grate onion and add with salt and pepper.
Mix again.
Chill thoroughly for 3 hours.

title: bluegill parmesan
directions: Place butter in a shallow dish. In another dish, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings. Dip fillets in butter, then coat with crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in saltwater 10 to 15 minutes; drain.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken broth, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add cauliflower.
Bring to boil; add cheese.
Sprinkle chives over each serving.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on cookie sheet, but do not take them apart. Bake until golden brown and let cool. Mix cream cheese and dry seasonings together. Spread mixture on baked crescent rolls and sprinkle on all chopped veggies. Let chill and serve.

title: billy faye's chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat on low until melted and fairly smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: scott's sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all
ingredients and spoon in miniature muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and water (boiled 1 minute to syrup).
In bowl mix egg yolks, flour and milk; slowly add syrup. Return to stove; boil until thick.
Add vanilla; pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle top with crushed graham crackers.

title: plum cake(this is a surprise!)
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, plums, food coloring and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and pecans.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Glaze cake while still warm
after removing from pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain. Rinse in cold water.
Place half of the noodles in large baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 of the sauce.
Add half of the Mozzarella cheese, then half of the cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bone.
Line bottom and sides of greased 3-quart casserole dish with layer of tortillas.
Sprinkle with 2 or 3 tablespoons chicken stock. Layer with 1/2 can undiluted mushroom soup and 1/2 of other ingredients in the order listed.
Cover with another layer of tortillas; sprinkle with 2 or 3 tablespoons chicken stock and remaining ingredients.
Top the last layer of cheese with can of tomatoes with chilies.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sheila's potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine in skillet. Add to rest of ingredients in a rectangular dish; cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: cherry burgundy ice cream
directions: In saucepan, dissolve jello in 1/2 cup boiling water and juice from the cherries.
Cool slightly.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs well.
Add sugar; beat well.
Blend in the half and half.
Cut cherries into fourths and add to mixture; stir in vanilla and jello mixture last.
Pour into freezer canister.
Add milk until about 3/4 full.
An electric freezer takes about 15 minutes to freeze.

title: whipped cream supreme
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with assorted vegetables (tomatoes, cauliflower, green pepper, cucumber, celery, etc.).

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press flat into cookie sheet.
Join all creases.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in pan.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add vinegar, oil and water.
Bring to boil.
Add beets and cook over low heat 30 minutes or until thick.

title: old fashion pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugars and all spices well.
Beat eggs well with 1/4 cup melted oleo or butter.
Add this to the pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 minutes longer.

title: strawberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour melted butter into a shallow, 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine flour, 1/4 cup sugar and milk.
Pour mixture evenly over butter.
Combine strawberries, remaining 1/2 cup sugar and water in a separate bowl, then spoon evenly over the flour/milk layer.
Do not stir. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry mixture.
Mix well.
Roll out desired amount on lightly floured surface to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully until you get the time right for your oven.
Dough will keep in refrigerator a week in covered container or plastic bag.

title: icebox pie
directions: Blend ingredients well in blender.
(If making lemon icebox pie, blend juice from 2 lemons in blender with cottage cheese.) Pour mixture into a bowl.
Add 1 vanilla supplement and mix well.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Place chicken, water, salt and pepper in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth.
Skim fat from broth.
Strain broth.

title: crab gumbo
directions: Heat oil in large kettle on medium heat.
Add flour, stirring constantly until dark brown but not burned.
Add onion and garlic. Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in undrained tomatoes.
Add sugar, worcestershire sauce, salt, hot pepper sauce and bay leaf.
Stir to break up tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes to blend flavor, stirring occasionally.
Add okra.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add crab.
Stir gently and heat through. Discard bay leaf.
Serve gumbo over rice.
(4 servings.)

title: tarheel pie
directions: Melt margarine; pour over chocolate chips until dissolved. Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, and nuts.
Mix with chocolate mixture.
Place in deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili with rice
directions: Combine kidney beans, Northern beans, undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, pepper, onion, chili powder, sugar, basil, garlic and water in a large saucepan.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top each serving with 1/2 cup rice.
Serves 4.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in lemonade.
Add ginger ale and ice.
Serve.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients like pie dough; roll to size of walnut.
Set on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in a double boiler.
Leave the pan of water under the melted chocolate while dipping the balls.
Set on wax paper on cookie sheet and cool.
Store in tight container in refrigerator.

title: patty's peanut butter icing
directions: Mix together and beat at high speed for at least 5 minutes.

title: quick and easy pizza
directions: You don't have to toast muffins.

title: mushroom-cheese souffle("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Start heating oven to 300°.
With hand beater, beat egg yolks until light and foamy.
Stir milk gradually into flour.
Add to egg yolks and beat well.
Add salt, pepper and cheese and beat until blended.
Gently fold in onion, mushrooms and egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Turn into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake about 50 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Makes 2 servings.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt the butter in saucepan. Stir in the brown sugar. Cook 2 minutes on low heat, stirring constantly. Add the milk, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Stir in the confectioners sugar gradually. Add the vanilla and mix well. Spread immediately on cake.
Frost 1 pound cake or 2 layers.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Place the eggs, pineapple juice, sugar and salt in a saucepan and blend and cook until it boils.
Cool.

title: savory oven-fried eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice eggplant into 1/2-inch slices. Beat eggs slightly.
Drop crumbs and seasonings into blender jar and blend well.
Pour crumbs on plate.
Grease 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan or baking pan with Crisco; heat pan for several minutes in hot oven.
Dip eggplant in egg and then into crumbs.
Place on hot baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes on each side.
Serve immediately with lemon slices.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: In large bowl, combine pears, sugar and pecans.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour large tube pan. Using wooden spoon, stir into pear mixture the oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Chill broth so fat will raise.
Mix cornstarch and broth together.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir in milk, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Bring to boil.
Cool and garnish with paprika.

title: sin cake
directions: Mix flour, melted oleo and nuts.
Spread in pan; bake approximately 20 minutes at 350° or until light brown.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thick; spread over 2nd layer.
Spread cherry pie filling over all.
Cover with the balance of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix with cream cheese until smooth.
Add seasoning.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: party chicken breast bake
directions: Lightly
grease baking dish.
Flatten breasts and place slice of	chipped
beef
and
shredded cheese on each breast. Roll
up each
breast
with ends down.
Place in baking dish. Combine soup and
sour
cream
and spoon over rolled breasts. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: mexican hero sandwiches
directions: Saute ground beef and onion in skillet until ground beef is brown.
Stir frequently.
Add chilies, olives, catsup, salt and chili powder and mix well.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Place one slice Colby cheese on bottom half of each loaf.
Spoon ground beef mixture over cheese.
Arrange bacon slice and Muenster cheese slice over ground beef.
Cover with remaining loaf halves.
Wrap loaves with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in beaten eggs.
Shake chicken in a bag of flour (plus a little cornstarch).
Deep fry until brown.
Place chicken in baking dish, cover with cashews, onion and sauce.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican bites
directions: Blend all ingredients, except muffins.
Toast muffins until half dark.
Top with mixture and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut into 4 pieces.

title: tomato shrimp aspic
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over cold water.
Stir in sugar, salt, lemon juice and hot tomato juice until it's dissolved.
Add shrimp, celery, onion and olives.
Pour into mold and leave overnight. When ready to serve, set in hot water for a few seconds and unmold on platter. Arrange salad greens around outside and serve with side dish of salad dressing.

title: helen's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs and flavorings thoroughly.
Measure flour and sift.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together. Blend well and chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut with a 3-inch cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut onions, celery, potatoes and add water.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Melt margarine; add flour and make paste.
Remove from pan; put in milk and heat.
Add roux gradually (margarine and flour).
Stir until creamy.
Add potatoes and corn.
Heat and stir.
Don't let boil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well.
Put in glass baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: parslied ham and swiss cheese sandwiches
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients and spread on sandwich buns. Fill with ham and cheese slices.
Wrap in foil and bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Sprinkle half of cheese over Crispy Pizza Crust; set aside. Saute vegetables, garlic and Italian seasoning in hot oil 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are barely crisp-tender. Spoon vegetables evenly onto pizza. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 450 degrees 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Yield: one 12-inch pizza.

title: quick veggie soup
directions: In large pot, brown meat and onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain; salt and pepper to taste.
Put in remaining ingredients; stir.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add milk to the line in your churn. Add sugar, sweetened condensed milk, and vanilla. Mix well. Add the beaten eggs last and keep the paddle on the churn stirring until you get the freezer ready. This will prevent the eggs from settling to the bottom. Churn and enjoy!

title: three cheese cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients with hands and form a ball.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, saving 1/2 cup broth.
Mix chicken, soups and milk.
Pour in a greased glass 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with Stove Top stuffing.
Mix 1/2 cup chicken broth with 1/2 stick melted butter; pour over top.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix until crumbly the first 5 ingredients.
Press 1/2 of crumbs in greased 7 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with rhubarb.
Then combine in saucepan the next 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut in squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into small cubes and boil until just tender. Drain and add onion, salt and pepper.
Combine vinegar, 1/3 cup mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons of hot water.
Add mixture to warm potatoes and let cool.
Add green peppers, pimento, celery and the other 1/2 cup mayonnaise to potato mixture and mix well.
Chill.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour and cinnamon together and add alternately with milk.
Add sherry, nuts and fruit.
Drop on well-greased cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Makes about 12 dozen.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with coffee.
Fold in chopped apples and raisins.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Cake may be iced when cool.

title: chicken and corn soup
directions: Bone chicken and discard skin.
Mince the chicken and combine with 1 teaspoon cornstarch and the egg whites, beaten until frothy.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Dissolve remaining cornstarch in water and add gradually to broth.
Add chicken mixture, corn, sherry and soy sauce and simmer a few minutes. Serve garnished with ham (boiled, baked or most flavorful and closest to the Chinese, Smithfield ham).
Serves 4.

title: chicken, zucchini and red pepper stir-fry
directions: Cut away tendon and any excess fat from chicken breasts.
Place in freezer just until chicken firms up for easier slicing.
Do not freeze solid.
Meanwhile, insert metal chopping blade in mixer bowl of food processor.
Process garlic (or chop fine with French knife).
Remove chopping blade and insert slicing blade.
